# Whitelist approach: ignore everything by default, then re-include only what's needed.
# vsce always bundles package.json regardless of ignore rules; README.md, LICENSE,
# and CHANGELOG.md are also auto-recognized by vsce, but re-include them for clarity.

# Ignore everything
*

# Re-include essential metadata
!package.json
!README.md
!LICENSE
!CHANGELOG.md

# Re-include built extension bundles (only what esbuild actually generates)
!dist/
!dist/extension.js
!dist/comparison.js
!dist/runOptions.js
!dist/initialization.js
